<p class="artwork">Sir Joseph Bowley's</h2>
<p class="artist">John Leech </p>
<p class="artdate">1844</p>
<p class="medium">Wood engraving</p>
<p class="size">12.3 cm by 7.3 cm (4 &frac34; by 2 &frac78; inches), vignetted.</p>
<p>Full-page illustration for Dickens's <span class="book">The Chimes</span>: "The Second 
Quarter," 55.</p> 

<p class="comment">[Click on image to enlarge it.]</p>
<p class="comment">The door was opened by a Porter. Such a Porter! Not of Toby’s order. 
Quite another thing. His place was the ticket though; not Toby’s. ["The Second Quarter," 
53]</p>
<p class="photographer">Scanned image and text by
<a href="../../../misc/pvabio.html">Philip V. Allingham</a>.</p>
