<p class="tc">Left: Charles Green's far more realistic version of Trotty's meeting the 
haughty functionary: <span class="tcartwork">Trotty and Sir Joseph Bowley's</span> 
(1912). Right: Fred Barnard's <span class="tcartwork">The Poor Man's Friend</span>, a 
study of the self-centred, pontificating Sir Joseph and his fashionably dressed, vacuous 
wife. [Click on images to enlarge them.]</p>

